{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"what-is-a-sitemap\"><a href=\"#what-is-a-sitemap\" aria-label=\"what is a sitemap permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is a Sitemap?</h3>\n<p>An <a href=\"https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/156184?hl=en\">XML sitemap</a> lists a website’s important pages, making sure search engines (such as Google) can find and crawl them all. In effect, a sitemap helps a search engine understand your website structure.</p>\n<p>Think of it as a map for your website. It shows what all of the pages are on your website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"install\"><a href=\"#install\" aria-label=\"install permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install</h3>\n<p>To generate an XML sitemap, you will use the <a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-sitemap/\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-plugin-sitemap</code></a> package. To install this package, run the following command:\n<code class=\"language-text\">npm install --save gatsby-plugin-sitemap</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"how-to-use-gatsby-plugin-sitemap\"><a href=\"#how-to-use-gatsby-plugin-sitemap\" aria-label=\"how to use gatsby plugin sitemap permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use <a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-sitemap/\">gatsby-plugin-sitemap</a></h3>\n<p>Once installation is complete, we can now add this plugin to our <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code>, like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">gatsby-config.js</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  siteMetadata<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    siteUrl<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`https://www.example.com`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-plugin-sitemap`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Next run a build (<code class=\"language-text\">npm run build</code>) since the sitemap generation will only happen for production builds. This is all that’s required to get a working sitemap with Gatsby! By default, the generated sitemap path is /sitemap.xml and will include all of your site’s pages, but of course the plugin exposes options to configure this default functionality.</p>\n<h3 id=\"additional-modification\"><a href=\"#additional-modification\" aria-label=\"additional modification permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Additional Modification</h3>\n<p>Additional modification steps are available in the <a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-sitemap\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-plugin-sitemap</code> documentation</a></p>","excerpt":"What is a Sitemap? An  XML sitemap  lists a website’s important pages, making sure search engines (such as Google) can find and crawl them…","timeToRead":1,"fields":{"slug":"/docs/creating-a-sitemap/","anchor":"creating-a-sitemap"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Creating a sitemap","overview":null,"issue":null},"parent":{"__typename":"File","relativePath":"docs/creating-a-sitemap.md"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/creating-a-sitemap/"}}